>   In Fluidity, players become a sloshing, flowing pool of water with an
  important mission. Players tilt, twist and flick the Wii Remote controller to
  splash and gush past challenging obstacles in Aquaticus, an illustrated
  encyclopedia. Players can unlock additional powers, such as the ability to
  freeze into a slick ice block that can shatter. Or players can boil the water
  and become a menacing vapor cloud with the power to shoot lightning. Players
  need all these abilities to conquer the dangerous chapters within Aquaticus.

    Fluidity offers detailed tutorials that introduce basic game mechanics, but
  the complexity quickly ramps up as special powers are acquired and enemies are
  introduced, testing players reflexes and ingenuity.
